    <h2>Uv Defense for People, Furniture, and Flooring</h2>
    <p>UV is relentless, and it doesn’t care if you’re in a sunroom in Chestnut Hill or a corner office in University City. One of the most trusted benefits of window tint in Philadelphia is UV defense for both people and interiors. Quick takeaways for Philadelphia: window film can improve comfort by reducing heat and glare at the glass. High-quality architectural window films from brands we offer—like 3M, Llumar, and Vista—can block up to 99% of UV radiation , helping protect skin and reduce the fading and breakdown you see on hardwood floors, area rugs, artwork, and upholstered furniture. It’s not just “sunlight”; it’s the invisible part of it that does long-term damage, and the benefits of window tint in Philadelphia can be a real advantage for spaces with bright, daily exposure. It also matters what standard glass does and doesn’t do. The Skin Cancer Foundation notes that UVB rays can be filtered and do not penetrate glass , while UVA can penetrate windows —which is one reason UV-focused film is so valuable for daily exposure near bright windows. (Source: Skin Cancer Foundation information on UVA/UVB ) If UV defense is your top priority, review our UV-blocking window film options .</p>
  </div>
</section>

